caption: This spot is excellent! Good prices, big portions and the employees are regularly super friendly.
My fiancé & I came here for the first time during the pandemic. It was pretty nice! We both liked how quaint it is! 🤗 We really enjoyed our delicious food! The Wild Rice item is SO yummy!!
Best corned beef i ever had.  Nice friendly comfortable atmosphere
This restaurant has superb service as well as delightful meals. One of the best restaurant ever. The drinks and food came out quick and the prices are economical. I recommend this place.
Awesome and delicious food, I liked the mood this place has, and the employees were nice. Will definitely eat here again.
Exceptional food, nice staff, constantly  awesome vibes. They charge convenient prices and the food quality is excellent. Highly recommended.

From the moment  you come to this place  the waiters give you a nice feeling. Very congenial stuff, it is a nice restaurant to  pass time with your friends or with your date. delightful  cooking, creative  chef, comfortable  cost and courteous  service. Warmly recommended.
Good atmosphere n food .  staff very friendly

Neighborhood gem! Dine in or take out. Delicious food! Friendly staff! Appreciate your dedication to the community, especially during the pandemic. Looking forward to many more memorable meals with family and friends, in a warm, welcoming local eatery.
The corn beef and cabbage was fantastic.

Someone suggested we try this restaurant and after seeing that they offer contactless curbside pickup we decided to give it a try. (We are in the COVID days and have multiple high risk people in our household). Unfortunately, when my husband showed up to pick up the food, curbside wasn’t an option and he had to go inside to get the food. Nobody in the restaurant was wearing masks. We both ended up sick with stomach aches, the runs & vomiting- unsure if it is related or not but we aren’t planning to go back
I just enjoyed their food. I always get awesome customer service here. The place is neat and the staff members are always friendly. Would recommend to others.
This spot is worth visiting. They have big portions for fair prices. Consistently well organized and with awesome mood. I highly recommend this place.
The place offers an awesome range of fresh food. I enjoy eating here. Staff members are always friendly, prices are affordable and the spot is always neat.

What a nice place!!! The only way to try a pub, bar or casual place is going back to basics, if basics are good, (the way l see it, at least), everything will fall in to the right place. On my first visit l tried the "OUR BURGER", with fries & ofcourse, plain mayo. What a blessing, it has been a very long time since l don't taste a real grilled burger & bun!!! Those pieces of charcoaled crust on top of the bun & the mix of lettuce, tomato, bacon & melted cheese just burst in my mouth bringing so many memories of how a real burger is done, meat, bread fire & expertise... ...you must try it! Oh & the RADIGAN'S DRAFT as the perfect partner to complete the art... Now, l don't even want to start with the atmosphere, great music, friendly guests, & great people taking care of you, right in the right moment... ...what are you still reading??? Go & try it!!! This place is a must
Exceptional spot to buy some food when in a rush. The service is efficient, pricing is affordable, awesome mood. I highly recommend this place

Great spot. Joanne is the best and Pat is the man. Good food and lots of beer on tap. A great local spot for anyone from Molloy. Also my friend Doug tried to kiss me here once. That was whackadoo for sure. I love the appetizer eggrolls as well.

Went there after all day at the vineyards with family. As always food was delicious. I have been there a lot and have never been disappointed by the food. My favourites are the BLT Quesadilla, Eggplant chips and grilled Romaine salad. Can’t wait to go back!!!

We were going to see a show at the Madison Theatre at Molloy College and looking to get a drink and a bite to eat before. It couldn't get any more convenient than Radigans Pub which was right up the block. They have a large selection of wine by the glass and good selection of local brews on tap. There were 6 of us at the table and all ordered something different and everyone enjoyed their meal. The menu contains a wide selection of soups, sandwiches, burgers and your standard pub fare. They also have a nice selection of entrees and specials of the day so there is something for everyone.
